The paper focuses on the physical layer security and energy efficiency of a heterogeneous cloud radio access network (C-RAN) with massive multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) technology. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as it deals with the study of communication systems and their properties, including secrecy and interference management. The paper also discusses the deployment of remote radio heads (RRHs) and macrocell base stations, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of soft fractional frequency reuse to mitigate inter-tier interference suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. The use of massive MIMO technology is a key aspect of the paper, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the paper discusses the overall energy efficiency of the network, which could place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category.
